==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Anemoscope
<hw>A*nem"o*scope</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ wind
+ -scope: cf. F. <ets>an⟦eacute⟧moscope</ets>.]</ety> <def>An instrument
which shows the direction of the wind; a wind vane; a weathercock; --
usually applied to a contrivance consisting of a vane above, connected
in the building with a dial or index with pointers to show the changes
of the wind.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Anemosis</ent>⟦br⟧
